387
00:46:51,963 --> 00:47:21,733
So if we look at the Buddha, once he'd become fully liberated, from then on all his actions are moving along a similar psychology, an idea comes, you know, I'll go and teach these people my old companion, and then he reinforces the idea, it's an intention, he's empowered it, and he's walked a couple of hundred, I think it's about a hundred miles or so, can you remember how much it was?

388
00:47:22,945 --> 00:47:50,134
it's a long way, it's a long way, at least a day so from where he was liberated to go and find these companions right up in Benares, Varanasi was an act of will but that whole process and going there and teaching did not produce another self

389
00:47:51,092 --> 00:47:51,855
See?

390
00:47:51,875 --> 00:47:53,778
So that idea of a self has gone.

391
00:47:53,858 --> 00:48:02,297
Now, does that mean that the Buddha doesn't have a sense of himself as it were?

392
00:48:02,938 --> 00:48:08,530
Like it's a sort of schizophrenia or an uncentered personality?

393
00:48:09,231 --> 00:48:11,936
Like, I mean, what's happening if he doesn't have a self, you see?

394
00:48:12,523 --> 00:48:19,315
Well, the thing is that it depends how you want to express this.

395
00:48:19,396 --> 00:48:36,927
The way I personally express it is that once this satipaññña, this intuitive intelligence, has discovered its own true nature, it forms a very different relationship to this body-mind complex, which is

396
00:48:37,987 --> 00:49:06,425
this this this personality this character this this body right it doesn't see it as me it's simply a vehicle like you might get in your car so if you get in your car and then say this is me they probably take you away slowly yes come on dear see but you don't say that you say I'm in I mean you might say it's my car you have a sort of a relationship to it but you don't say it's me

397
00:49:06,675 --> 00:49:10,690
So it's the same with this Satipaññā, this Buddha within us.

398
00:49:11,293 --> 00:49:13,000
It no longer says, this is me.

399
00:49:13,481 --> 00:49:15,690
It's coming from some other place.

400
00:49:16,547 --> 00:49:37,007
and it's driven by similar, on a wholesome level it's driven by similar attitudes of love, compassion, joy but this time it's not being corrupted, it doesn't have the kink of a self in it in other words, what's in it for me?

401
00:49:38,929 --> 00:49:41,813
coming from a pure heart, a pure wisdom base

402
00:49:43,632 --> 00:50:02,501
So now that is, I think, a more acceptable way of understanding rebirth, and I think it's a way that allows us to use the concept of rebirth very much as part of our spiritual practice.

403
00:50:02,666 --> 00:50:06,130
So here I am being reborn as a greedy person again.

404
00:50:06,731 --> 00:50:07,231
You see what I mean?

405
00:50:07,271 --> 00:50:09,074
It's like, here I go again.

406
00:50:09,315 --> 00:50:09,875
It's me again.

407
00:50:10,034 --> 00:50:10,315
Hello.

408
00:50:11,257 --> 00:50:12,798
And it's sort of recognizing that.

409
00:50:12,818 --> 00:50:15,400
I say, you greedy person, you see.

410
00:50:15,442 --> 00:50:16,922
Not damning, of course, not judging.

411
00:50:17,543 --> 00:50:24,351
But simply no longer enjoining it, no longer indulging in that.

412
00:50:24,371 --> 00:50:24,692
Yeah?

413
00:50:25,617 --> 00:50:27,719
So now, what happens when we die?

414
00:50:27,818 --> 00:50:29,601
So this is the next big thing, you see.

415
00:50:29,641 --> 00:50:31,382
What happens then when we die?

416
00:50:31,463 --> 00:50:37,989
Well, in terms of spiritual practice, it's irrelevant because all we have is this present moment.

417
00:50:38,170 --> 00:50:39,692
You're either practicing or you're not.

418
00:50:40,793 --> 00:50:44,076
When you die, well, if you're not anymore, fine.

419
00:50:44,096 --> 00:50:45,117
There's no suffering there.

420
00:50:46,199 --> 00:50:48,581
You won't be bothered at all if you disappear completely.

421
00:50:50,083 --> 00:50:53,346
On the other hand, if you reappear, then it might...

422
00:50:54,202 --> 00:51:23,990
if you actually reappear then of course there's a problem again you're stuck with this being here I am again it's like when you wake up in the morning isn't it here I am again what we're doing you know like you wake up where have I been so all of a sudden and I I just read a quote about that in the final chapter on the question do you remember the quote

423
00:51:24,612 --> 00:51:31,730
Along the lines of, if there is no such thing as rebirth, but you've lived an honourable life, well, that's all very good.

424
00:51:32,753 --> 00:51:35,500
And you've lived a life of happiness and peace.

425
00:51:40,255 --> 00:51:44,581
and you've lived recording, then your rebirth will be positive.

426
00:51:44,601 --> 00:51:45,282
That's right.

427
00:51:45,583 --> 00:51:47,144
A win-win situation.

428
00:51:47,224 --> 00:51:49,088
Yes, I know the Buddha points that out.

429
00:51:49,768 --> 00:51:53,594
Because obviously in his day too there were annihilationists, you know.

430
00:51:54,115 --> 00:51:56,760
The people who thought that when you died that was it.

431
00:51:56,880 --> 00:52:03,849
There were some people who had a more convoluted system where you went through all these different realms and then disappeared.

432
00:52:04,117 --> 00:52:07,822
but there were definitely annihilationists in his day.

433
00:52:08,663 --> 00:52:17,715
And yes, he gives this win-win situation where, you know, if you live a virtuous life, at least you get these benefits, and then fine, you disappear.

434
00:52:19,237 --> 00:52:27,728
And if you live a virtuous life and wake up somewhere else, then you've got at least the benefits of that, of your virtuous life, you see.

435
00:52:32,416 --> 00:52:59,992
the Buddha talks about the citta body, the body of the mind, the mental body which he says through meditative practices you can exit from the body like a sword from the scabbard take it out and I've been, I know people who have had this subtle body leave the physical body and go for a walk and come back

436
00:53:01,576 --> 00:53:12,030
and it still has the same unfortunate qualities as the physical body, it still arises and passes away, but it's just of this finer material.

437
00:53:13,331 --> 00:53:20,681
And that would be, in the Mahayana system, as I understand it, that's your

438
00:53:20,746 --> 00:53:50,280
body of bliss when it becomes enlightened that's your sambhogakaya this is known as your nirmanakaya which is your apparition body or something your creative the body that's created now in all this there's the dharmakaya or the buddha within you see and of course that's of a different nature and people experience that too outside their bodies those people who've had near death experiences

439
00:53:51,391 --> 00:53:58,416
where this consciousness has exited from this whole system and yet is obviously very conscious.

440
00:54:00,378 --> 00:54:06,764
So, in terms of rebirth, it's never caused me any problems.

441
00:54:07,505 --> 00:54:10,847
You know, the idea that one goes on in some way.

442
00:54:12,250 --> 00:54:19,356
But it's necessary to also understand that that belief is not necessary.

443
00:54:20,061 --> 00:54:42,710
Often when people come to Buddhism, if they've been brought up in one of the religions, the monotheistic religions, Christianity or Judaism or whatnot, it's like there's a misunderstanding that they have to believe what the Buddha says or else it's not going to work.

444
00:54:42,952 --> 00:54:46,996
It's like you believe that Jesus died to save us all.

445
00:54:47,146 --> 00:54:53,614
And you have to believe that or else you don't get your comeuppance, you don't get your grace, you see, you have to believe that.

446
00:54:54,253 --> 00:54:56,556
But of course, Buddhism is very different from that.

447
00:54:57,016 --> 00:55:07,909
It is very much a hypothesis, it's a theory that the Buddha puts to us and says, well, this is true for me, you'll have to find out for yourself whether it's true for you.

448
00:55:08,590 --> 00:55:09,492
You know what I mean?

449
00:55:09,512 --> 00:55:10,313
It's an investigation.

450
00:55:10,693 --> 00:55:14,637
And that process of investigation is the process of liberation.

451
00:55:16,576 --> 00:55:22,001
So, I can take out the salient points of this question.

452
00:55:25,465 --> 00:55:36,614
Yeah, so then what happens, I mean, you know, if all human beings disappeared, well, that'd be it, the Earth would be liberated from very deluded beings.

453
00:55:36,635 --> 00:55:38,016
That's for sure.

454
00:55:38,536 --> 00:55:42,260
Probably feel very Mother Earth and feel joy if you jump up and down with joy.

455
00:55:42,760 --> 00:55:43,782
Yippee!

456
00:55:44,605 --> 00:55:47,969
Well, she's got rid of a few species every so often.

457
00:55:47,989 --> 00:55:49,311
She just shakes them off, doesn't she?

458
00:55:49,913 --> 00:55:52,898
And then sort of reinvigorates herself and starts again.

459
00:55:55,362 --> 00:55:55,742
Wonderful.

460
00:55:56,923 --> 00:56:09,043
Now, this question about all beings, it's just that I know it's a hypothetical question, but it reminds me of a lovely question that was asked by...

461
00:56:09,681 --> 00:56:14,407
by a woman of Jnanapanika, who was this German monk.

462
00:56:14,748 --> 00:56:17,851
He's the one who started the Buddhist Publication Society in Kandy.

463
00:56:18,773 --> 00:56:26,581
And she said to him, in a similar vein, supposing everybody became monks and nuns.

464
00:56:26,601 --> 00:56:29,786
See, you know, like that would be the end of the human race, you see.

465
00:56:30,427 --> 00:56:33,650
And he said, my dear, it won't happen.

466
00:56:37,856 --> 00:56:38,996
It just won't happen.

467
00:56:39,280 --> 00:56:49,271
So, even though I know this is a hypothetical question, if all human beings became liberated all at once, it just won't happen.

468
00:56:54,157 --> 00:56:58,983
But the question goes on and says, life manifesting itself is all in wonderment.

469
00:56:59,583 --> 00:57:04,409
Now, the Buddha is definitely aware of beauty,

470
00:57:05,032 --> 00:57:33,030
even in the very simple way of the way he asked his order the monks and nuns to robe you remember in the early days they were happy with just taking bits of cloth off the charnel grounds where they put dead bodies in shrouds and cut it into pieces, sewed it together, anything would do but when he saw a group of his monks dressed like this he didn't like it at all when he saw it as a way of manifesting his teaching

471
00:57:33,010 --> 00:57:41,483
And that's when he asked them to cut it into various pieces and sew it in such a way that it looked like paddy fields.

472
00:57:42,063 --> 00:57:42,844
That's what they looked like.

473
00:57:43,826 --> 00:57:52,739
And to dye it, to boil it with this nut called an arakanut, which gives it a sort of light brown colour.

474
00:57:55,505 --> 00:58:13,771
And if you read the final discourse, which leads to his passing, which leads to his parinirvana, he's walking along with Ananda, his companion, his assistant, and he says, well, this lovely food, let's go and eat this in a lovely shrine.

475
00:58:14,271 --> 00:58:18,679
He doesn't say, let's just sit down here in this donkey and eat this stuff.

476
00:58:19,559 --> 00:58:21,623
He actually seeks out what is beautiful.

477
00:58:22,704 --> 00:58:24,347
And if you...

478
00:58:25,440 --> 00:58:30,007
If you think about it from, I think it's Plato, isn't it?

479
00:58:30,027 --> 00:58:32,431
Plato said, I think it's very true, isn't it?

480
00:58:32,871 --> 00:58:37,077
That with truth, with truth there arises virtue.

481
00:58:38,920 --> 00:58:40,282
And with virtue, beauty.

482
00:58:41,525 --> 00:58:45,931
So now, the truth is the intellect, it's understanding.

483
00:58:46,713 --> 00:58:51,981
Virtue is your will, how you manifest your understanding in daily life.

484
00:58:52,382 --> 00:58:54,063
And beauty is the heart.

485
00:58:54,331 --> 00:58:55,072
It's art.

486
00:58:55,333 --> 00:59:00,829
It's the way that you manifest your feeling, your...

487
00:59:02,273 --> 00:59:03,697
This question used the word love.

488
00:59:03,757 --> 00:59:04,862
I mean, that's what love is, isn't it?

489
00:59:07,228 --> 00:59:07,750
So...

490
00:59:09,079 --> 00:59:10,440
The Buddha doesn't deny that.

491
00:59:10,481 --> 00:59:12,543
He doesn't deny that's what life is.

492
00:59:12,583 --> 00:59:15,226
That's what I definitely understand by it.

493
00:59:15,987 --> 00:59:19,329
And I shall sort of end with a little story.

494
00:59:19,349 --> 00:59:21,552
I think I've answered the question.

495
00:59:22,012 --> 00:59:33,824
End with a little story about this young girl who turned up at the monastery at Kandaboda, which is my monastery in Sri Lanka.

496
00:59:34,804 --> 00:59:37,246
And her father said that

497
00:59:38,442 --> 01:00:06,356
every evening she would come and tell him that she was going to a particular heavenly realm because she was writing the biography of the Buddha so she was only a little girl nine or ten or something so he you know he sort of humored her and said oh yeah very good you know so she got to bed you see anyway one day it would seem you can only believe what people tell you she got fed up with her dad and rose up in front of him and disappeared

498
01:00:07,382 --> 01:00:13,731
So he rushed her off to this monastery, Khandabodha, with this big question, you see, and she came along.

499
01:00:14,833 --> 01:00:17,418
And her answers are on a tape.

500
01:00:17,438 --> 01:00:29,695
They're in Sinhalese, so I don't understand it, but the gist of it was that she was an Arahant, and she didn't bow to monks.

501
01:00:29,715 --> 01:00:33,501
And she didn't, because she was completely liberated.

502
01:00:34,824 --> 01:00:35,684
And

503
01:00:36,036 --> 01:01:00,728
she had come back to help her grandfather this particular person and when she went up to this particular heavenly realm all the Buddhas the Buddha and all the disciples were there and there were shrines where they came and gave talks now it's a strange thing isn't it I don't know whether you have to believe this or not

504
01:01:00,943 --> 01:01:09,860
So many about three or four years later I went back to Sri Lanka and I asked about this girl but unfortunately she disappeared.

505
01:01:09,880 --> 01:01:11,643
She'd now be I suppose 20, 20-odd.

506
01:01:11,664 --> 01:01:18,155
It would be interesting to try and seek her out and find out whether she was dreaming or not.

507
01:01:18,215 --> 01:01:24,166
But her father said she rose up in front of him and disappeared.

508
01:01:24,603 --> 01:01:41,751
no mind you Jesus you know the Ascension so there are wonderful things in the world so unless there are questions arising

509
01:01:50,067 --> 01:01:53,275
I trust that my words have been of some assistance.

510
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:59,132
May you be liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

